Key Match Events: Egypt's goalkeeper Mohamed Abou Gabal missed his penalty in the shootout as the Democratic Republic of Congo claimed an epic 8-7 victory
Mohamed Bayo scored a last-gasp winner to send Guinea into the last eight of the Africa Cup of Nations
Post-Match Reflections: The Guinea coach, Kaba Diawara, said, 'It was a very satisfying victory. We had a lot of criticism after our group games but my players got due reward for all of their work'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match between Egypt and DR Congo went to a shootout, with DR Congo winning 8-7
The match between Guinea and Equatorial Guinea ended with a late winner by Guinea's Mohamed Bayo
Others: The Africa Cup of Nations 2023 is ongoing
Several players received red cards, including Mohamed Hamdy of Egypt and Federico Bikoro of Equatorial Guinea
